definition: many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"
wheel/disk/ring/steamship/to take turns/to rotate/by turn/classifier for big round objects: disk, or recurring events: round, turn

sentences.english: Currently, venture capital activities are multi-round investments.
sentences.chinese: 當前，風險投資活動大多采用多輪投資的方式。

sentences.english: Chinese and South Korean diplomatic authorities have held many rounds of negotiations on the handling of the issue.
sentences.chinese: 中韓雙方外交部門就如何解決此問題進行了多輪磋商。

sentences.english: Control method of electronic differential of EV with four in-wheel motors;
sentences.chinese: 採用輪轂電機多輪驅動是電動汽車發展的新方向。

sentences.english: So activity listing may go through several risk-control iterations.
sentences.chinese: 整個活動表可能經過多輪這樣的風險控制過程。

sentences.english: After several rounds with the rat and the bar, Watson then brought out the rat on its own.
sentences.chinese: 在多輪“小鼠和鐵棒”的實驗後，華生單獨給出小鼠。

sentences.english: Expert poker players prefer poker games with many rounds.
sentences.chinese: 專家級牌手更喜歡多輪的遊戲。
